About SEED:
The mission of SEED schools is to prepare scholars academically, socially, and emotionally, for success in and beyond college in a public, college-prep, boarding school setting.

The SEED Public Charter School of Washington D.C. (SEED DC) opened in 1998 as the nation’s first urban public college preparatory boarding school. SEED DC empowers over 250 scholars in grades 8-12 to achieve their full potential within our 24-hour learning environment and exposure opportunities. By the year 2020-2021, SEED will serve grades 9-12 only as we transition to providing more high-quality, high school seats to families in the District. All SEED scholars live on campus between Sunday evenings and Friday afternoons.

Our innovative model integrates a rigorous academic program with a nurturing boarding program that teaches life skills and provides a safe and secure environment. This boarding school model provides a comprehensive solution to the challenges facing urban youth and serves as a prototype for expansion nationwide. Our model has proven successful: over 90 percent of SEED graduates have been accepted to four-year colleges and universities throughout the country and over 60 percent remain enrolled in college or already have earned college degrees.

* More information can be found on the school’s website: www.seedschooldc.org

Position Overview
The Data Analyst, having both analytical and instructional expertise, works alongside school leadership and staff to support the continuous improvement of student learning and school operations. The primary responsibilities include coordinating the systemic collection of information, effective management of data systems, and ensuring accurate analysis for both compliance and continuous improvement purposes.

The Data Analyst serves as the point-of-contact (POC) to support and monitor the preparation of data submission, statistical reports on educational activities for government and educational agencies (OSSE & DC PCSB) through different information systems (e.g. PowerSchool, Quickbase, Box, Qlik Sense, SunGuard K-12, Socrata, Power BI, R, etc.).

The Data Analyst develops standard templates for reporting and analysis to drive data-driven practices to include data tables, charts and analyses that provide a comprehensive picture of how the school is performing on key indicators of success. The Data Analyst plays a key role in student and school success by assisting the Head of School (HOS) and senior leadership team in discovering high leverage insights from the data.

Areas of Responsibility & Accountability:
Provide ongoing data analysis for instructional team in a timely fashion to support instructional resource allocation;
Utilize PowerSchool, the school’s student information systems (SIS), for the collection and management of student data;
Ensure data is accurate and up-to-date; perform regularly-scheduled data checks and identify data errors; correct data errors or manage a process for data corrections with the Office of the State Superintendent of Education (OSSE) and the Pubic Charter School Board (PCSB);
